---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PilotBuilder from '../components/PilotBuilder.tsx';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Step 6: Pilot" step={6} prev={`${base}5-bound/`} next={`${base}7-evaluate/`}>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto py-10 px-4 landing-content">

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1>Build the pilot plan</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Assemble everything into a roadmap you can execute and a brief you can hand to a builder.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <p>
        You have a design and you have set boundaries. Now define how you will actually test it. A pilot is not "turn it on and see what happens." It is a structured test with clear criteria for what success looks like and what would cause you to stop.
      </p>

      <p>
        This page produces two outputs: a roadmap for the decision maker (what we are testing, how we measure, what the timeline is) and a build brief for the implementer (components, boundaries, connections, specific questions).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <PilotBuilder client:load />
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .landing-content .subtitle {
    color: var(--text-light);
    font-size: 15px;
  }
</style>
